picID=804.topic&index=110>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't hate you Blizz</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> actually i know of several Vision that where shopping for new guilds due to the palimax view of loot.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hurrah!  You've managed to point out what I already said.  What isn't true, however, is that we were EVER on the verge of collapse, which is what the unguilded guy keeps trying to say.<br>
<br>
Of course people shop guilds all the time.  Unless you're a GL or recruitment officer for a guild you have NO IDEA how many people are constantly shopping guilds.  Some of them are trying to find the right fit.  Some of them are trying to get more stuff for themselves.  What guild has the policies that give me the most stuff...  ....hrm....<br>
<br>
Any person who's ever done staffing would be proud of our turn-over rate, and many people who leave Vision ask to come back (and some of them even mature enough that we TAKE them back - heh).<br>
<br>
Also, you make a HUGE mistake in assuming they want to leave because of MY view of loot.  For starters, I don't make the policies at Vision.  I'm part of the process, but I'm only one of a handful of officers with that power.  Second, most items are given out by people other than me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> and its not very fair to say &quot;this ranger deserve it more because he has been to 3 more raids then you&quot; <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I disagree.  In some cases it's VERY fair to say exactly that.  <br>
<br>
Of course, the best part is, in Vision, we're pretty up-front about it.  You know what you're in for.  If you don't like the policies, it's not like we shoved 'em down your throat.  You OPTED to have them.  In fact, if it was your class' loot, you got to work with your CL to set that policy.  Every Ranger, for example, gets to talk to Cheeta and decide how their policy is going to work.  The rule is that they all have to agree that they like them -- or at least agree that they're fair and they can live with 'em.  So, if someone's complaining about the way *I* distribute loot, they need to understand either they disagree with our philosphy entirely, or that they simply didn't do a good job of working with their class and their officers to find a better solution*.<br>
<br>
....the best part is, that if anyone ever left Vision over loot, they're a liar; as they've always given another reason.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> [*For example, people suggest point systems for us all the time, then I ask them to track one that takes things like ports and the guy who made potions into account, and to keep tally for a month.  When they fail, I ask them what other suggestions they have.  :)  ]</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
